C) Compile Error
D) NullReferenceException

43. Delegates have interesting capturing mechanisms. What gets written to output?
var actions = new List<Action>();
for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) { actions.Add(() => Console.Write(i)); }
foreach (var a in actions) a();
A) 012
B) 333
C) 222
D) 000

45. Method hiding using new vs overriding. What prints here?
class Parent { public void Show() => Console.Write("Parent"); }
class Child : Parent { public new void Show() => Console.Write("Child"); }
Parent p = new Child(); p.Show();
A) Parent
B) Child
C) Compile Error
D) Throws RuntimeBindException

